08frm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=1910.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showNextMessage?topicID=1910.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#cccccc class=headings><font color=#8b1a1a>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#cccccc class=headings><font color=#8b1a1a>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ublouder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blouder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/27/02 7:52:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1910.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Need weapon advice plz</span><hr size=1> I just started my monk recently. Been playing a druid for the most part for much of the last year. My question is and I am sure it has been covered before but just cant seem to find just what I need. I have the following weapons and need to know how to use them properly such as primary or secondary.<br>
I have a master wu's trance stick,Stave of shielding,fist of rock and 2 PSU. Need to know how to equip them to be the most deadly. Should I use the 2 staffs together or mix with a H2H weapon such as the fist of rock. Is it good to mix the 2 or not. I di have SCHW too if this helps. Thanks in advance for any help you can give.<br>
<br>
<br>
Luldur <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukalegeros.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalegeros</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/27/02 8:09:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1910.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~sneezer/panda2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need weapon advice plz</span><hr size=1> You'll probably do the most damage with the stave of shielding in your mainhand and either the wu's or fist of rock in your offhand.  The wu's and fist of rock will perform the same in solo situations (due to AC and hp on the fist, versus the small advantage of a bit of extra damage with smite at level 35 on the stick.)  The stave has by far the best ratio and damage output.  Personally I'd sell the other two weapons and look for a better overall mainhand weapon, look up the weapons post on the monk equipment forum. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=180047"><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~sneezer/panda.gif"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 4148<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/27/02 8:11:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1910.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need weapon advice plz</span><hr size=1> I'm thinking SoS/Fist of Rock if you want to max out your damage (for now), Wu's/Fist of Rock if you want to max your skills quickly.  That's the best advice I can give without knowing your specific level.<br>
<br>
Sell the PSU's, they are of no value compaired with the other weapons in speed or damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ublouder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blouder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/28/02 9:04:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1910.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need weapon advice plz</span><hr size=1> Sorry forgot to give my lvl I am at lvl 8 atm. From what I see so far its ok than to mix the 1hb and H2H weapons and this will still raise both skills? Any suggestions on what to look for as a weapon upgrade would be helpful also. Thanks again<br>
<br>
Luldur <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukasekill2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kasekill2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/28/02 10:56:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1910.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:</span><hr size=1> At your level the weapons with the best DMG ratio would be the most deadly in primary and I assume secondary also.  So use the SoS in prime and your choice between FoR and the trance stick in secondary.  I would use FoR untill the wu stick starts to proc.  <br>
<br>
Once dmg bonus starts to kick in the faster weapons start becoming more powerful in primary.  With a dmg bonus of 7 or 8 the jade mace (9/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  begins to out damage the SoS in primary.<br>
<br>
JM would be a nice upgrade the cost about 3k.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/28/02 11:02:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1910.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> While I have a friend who has done parses of Jade Mace versus Stave of Shielding in primary hand at 52 showing them to be about the same in DPS, modals state that Jade Mace will only outdamage Stave of Shielding in primary hand after attaining level 58 (at which point you probably have your epic, which is better than a Jade Mace)<br>
<br>
Also, Master Wu's Trance Stick is highly overrated.  It's ratio is not too great and the proc is often resisted.<br>
<br>
In all other points, I agree with Kasekill2.  Before level 28, use the weapons with the best ratio.  Once you get a damage bonus it becomes a consideration as well. <p>-Korph
<br>
<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308735"><img src="http://gjband.com/Sig.jpg"><br>Level 51 Disciple</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwhytspirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whytspirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/28/02 11:47:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1910.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://xtctripp101.homestead.com/files/Sigs/Whytspirit_sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> I personally used the Wu's and a H2H weapon for the first 20 levels or so to help build up both skills at the same time. I got started using the 2HB a bit later and it was nice to have only one skill to catch up on. The first of rock is great for training up the hand to hand.<br>
<br>
~Siska~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uz0nk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Z0nk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/30/02 8:14:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1910.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> Keep in mind that your damage is capped until level 20 or so...  SoS will act like a 10/28 weapon at level 8 <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=1910.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showNextMessage?topicID=1910.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1910.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.emailToFriend?topicID=1910.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.threadControl?topicID=1910.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1910.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.uns